These people are what makes the Italian health care system great. They might not have brand new beds (who cares!), but the personnel is absolutely brilliant and very knowledgable (like in other sectors). Unfortunately, the large number of old people in Italy (the oldest population in Europe and the second in the World after Japan) complicates things and, obviously, these people are not receiving the same treatment the rest is receiving due to limited human resources (not mentioning the Italian brain drain). Therefore, it is causing more deaths than in other countries. However, my main concern is with the UK, where I live...
PS I am an Italian myself and receive information from direct sources working in Italian hospitals.


Dear folks, this should be a lesson to learn about how to take care of ourself and, in particular, our wonderful planet, reminding that we are ALL GUESTS here and do not own anything, even our dear body which is merely a container of who we actually are.


Peace
